oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: 1911 Vanderbilt University football team
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Group portrait of the 1911 Vanderbilt University football team in uniform, featuring Ray Morrison (1885 - 1982), who is highlighted by a surround of black.

Ray Morrison was a quarterback for the Vanderbilt University football team, 1908 - 1911, and is widely considered one of Vanderbilt's greatest players. He later served as the first football coach at Southern Methodist University and is referred to as the "Father of the Forward Pass."
